Qt Hldplugin version 3.1 contains bug fixes and new features.

There is a total of about X changes by N individual contributors.

The most important changes are listed in this document. For a complete
list of changes, see the Git log for the Qt Hldplugin sources that
you can check out from the public Git repository. For example:

git clone git://gitorious.org/qt-hldplugin/qt-hldplugin.git
git log --cherry-pick --pretty=oneline origin/3.0..origin/3.1

General
   * Added support for "~" as an alias for the user's home directory in the directory in file
     system search (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-7753)
   * Added Beautifier plugin that allows to fix coding style of files with external coding
     style tools (Artistic Style, Clang-format, Uncrustify) (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-7489)

Editing
   * Added File > Reload for files that are open and unmodified in Qt Hldplugin but might be
     different on disk
   * Added option to not hide the mouse cursor while typing (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-3584)
   * Made visible margin configurable per project
   * Fixed reloading contents in binary editor (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-6275)
   * Fixed names and saving of custom locator filters (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11051)

Managing and Building Projects
   * Re-added option to import existing builds even after project configuration (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-7836)
   * Fixed that compiler output in issues list was not using monospace font (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11345)
   * Fixed crash when removing run configuration that was about to be run (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11594)

QMake Projects
   * Added context menu item "Add Existing Directory" that adds all
     files from a directory (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9081)
   * Added support for QMAKE_EXTRA_COMPILERS (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11212)
   * Fixed issues with absolute paths in TARGET

Qbs Projects
   * Added option for building with --check-timestamps
   * Fixed that compiler flags were not set (QBS-481)

Generic Projects
   * Added context menu item "Add Existing Directory" that adds all
     files from a directory (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9081)
   * Made importing files follow directory symlinks (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-8897)

Debugging
   * Removed support for GDB without Python
   * Added context menu item for saving backtrace as tasks-file
   * GDB, LLDB
      * Added pretty printers for std::unordered_set and boost::container::list
      * Fixed various pretty printers
   * CDB
      * Added pretty printer for std::complex and C++11 std::array
   * LLDB
      * Added support for debugging applications that run in terminal (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9650)
      * Added support for "Create Full Backtrace" (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11642)
      * Fixed that debugging was not possible with MallocScribble environment variable set
        (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11371)
      * Fixed "Jump to Line", "Run to Line" and "Jump to Address"
      * Fixed updating breakpoint locations while debugging (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11564)

QML Profiler
   * Improved performance (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10950)
   * Improved layout of details views
   * Added JavaScript calls in Events view and Timeline view
   * Fixed opening files from JavaScript profiling output (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11094)
   * Fixed hovering over narrow items in Timeline view (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11692)

C++ Support
   * Added code model inspector
   * Added experimental support for Clang-based code model
   * Added support for multiline strings and comments (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-662)
   * Fixed parsing of ??< ??> ??( ??) trigraphs (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-2474)
   * Fixed adding definition for function with rvalue-reference
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10555)
   * Fixed semantic highlighting after "Save as"
   * Fixed syntax highlighting of multiline strings and comments (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-662)
   * Fixed that symbol dropdown was jumping to the wrong editor (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11157)
   * Fixed highlighting when #undef is used (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10454)
   * Fixed issue with follow symbol and overloaded functions (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10295)
   * Improved the Insert Virtual Functions refactoring action:
       * Check only pure virtual functions by default
       * Display all overrides of a function
       * Do not include final functions

QML Support
   * Simplified Qt Quick Application templates (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11264)
   * Improved performance when using split views

Qt Quick Designer
   * Fixed selecting overlapping items with same z-value (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11066)
   * Fixed setting text alignment (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11054)
   * Fixed crash with anchors (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11138)
   * Fixed issue with warning text not being readable (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9603)

Diff Viewer
   * Fixed display of inserted lines at end of file (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11281)
   * Fixed handling of whitespace changes (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11002)

Version Control Systems
   * Git
      * Added visual indicator for affected commits when resetting and rebasing
      * Enabled option to push commit directly after fixup
      * Enabled choosing non-fast-forward merge when fast-forward is applicable
      * Added completion in change selection dialog
      * Fixed freeze after resolving conflict with cherry-pick or revert
      * Added support for local branch selection in the Push to Gerrit dialog
      * Removed branch list from "Git Show" header (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11293)
   * ClearCase
      * Improved performance of indexing dynamic views
      * Added warning when editing Derived Objects
   * Bazaar
      * Added support for uncommit command
   * Mercurial
      * Added current branch to project and window title

FakeVim
   * Added "gj", "gk", "g0", "g^" and "g$" commands
   * Added toggle ("!") and print ("?") options to "set" command
   * Added support for relative line numbering
   * Made dot command work for letter case commands in visual mode
   * Fixed backward incremental search (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-7251)

Platform Specific

Qt Support
   * Custom wizards now use class "qmakeproject" instead of "qt4project"

QNX
   * Added support for Python based pretty printers when debugging on devices
   * Added better error messages for common deployment errors
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9673, QTHLDPLUGINBUG-9001)
   * Added line and column information to text based BAR descriptor editor
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10395)
   * Added simple management of user debug tokens
   * Added simple management of runtime configurations
   * Added support for attaching debugger to running applications
   * Fixed several issues with certificate password dialog in BlackBerry
     options (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10948)
   * Fixed mkspec setting in the qmake build step (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11674)

Android
   * Made it possible to cancel waiting for an AVD to boot up
   * Added download buttons for Android toolkit parts to Options page
   * Added warning for invalid JDK setting (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11218)
   * Added minimal support for editing Java, with indentation of blocks and keyword completion
     (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11220)
   * Added Java file wizard (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11220)
   * Fixed opening Java files from error messages (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10904)
   * Fixed colors in AndroidManifest editor (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10597)
   * Fixed modified state of AndroidManifest editor (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-11163)
   * Fixed apply-behavior of Android Options page (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-7724)
   * Fixed that Qt Hldplugin restart was required after configuring Android SDK (QTHLDPLUGINBUG-10936)

iOS
   * Enabled iOS support by default
   * Added support for QML debugging
   * Added check for already running application on device
   * Added automatic detection that developer mode becomes activated on connected device

WinRT
   * Added experimental support

